      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm a consultant working with some C-suite executives who are pretty skeptical about our upcoming DEI training sessions. They feel like these programs actually undermine 'true' meritocracy and create a kind of reverse discrimination. Can you help me prep for this? I need you to play devil's advocate and build the strongest possible case for why race-blind meritocracy is more just than DEI initiatives. What would be the main arguments they'd use to say DEI is actually discriminatory?",
